oc:kn_002d7d39 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After generating copy output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Copywriting produces text output intended for publication on marketing pages. Generated copy may include SEO meta content (page title, meta description). Copy should be reviewed with the copy-editing skill before publication." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Published copy affects brand perception and conversion rates. A secondary editing pass catches issues the initial drafting phase misses." .

oc:kn_12a07dfe a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When crafting value propositions, headlines, and benefit sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Write benefits (what the customer gets) not features (what the product does). Use customer language from reviews, interviews, and support tickets rather than company jargon. Mirror voice-of-customer phrasing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Benefits connect to customer outcomes and emotions; features are product-centric. Customer language resonates because it matches how buyers already think about their problem." .

oc:kn_352b3ee3 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing transitional phrases between sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid AI-tell transition phrases: 'That being said,' 'It's worth noting that,' 'At its core,' 'In today's digital landscape,' 'Let's delve into.' Vary transitions and keep them natural—read aloud to test." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overused AI-generated phrases undermine credibility and trigger AI-writing detection, hurting both trust and SEO." .

oc:kn_987352b3 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring page copy and writing above-the-fold elements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each page section should advance exactly one argument. Build a logical flow down the page. Headlines communicate core value proposition, subheadlines add specificity (1-2 sentences max), and CTAs follow the formula: [Action Verb] + [What They Get] + [Qualifier]." ;
    oc:hasRationale "One idea per section creates a clear persuasive narrative. Overloaded sections confuse and lose readers. Structured CTAs that communicate value outperform generic ones." .

oc:kn_d78a4159 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any marketing copy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always prioritize clarity over cleverness. If you must choose between clear and creative, choose clear. Use simple words ('use' not 'utilize', 'help' not 'facilitate'), specific claims over vague ones, active voice, and confident statements without qualifiers like 'almost' or 'very'." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Confusion kills conversion. Visitors skim and decide in seconds—clarity ensures they understand the value proposition immediately." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_d9857265 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any copywriting task" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before writing, check for .agents/product-marketing-context.md (or .claude/product-marketing-context.md). Read it first and only ask for information not already covered. Gather four context areas: page purpose (type + primary action), audience (ideal customer, problem, objections, language), product/offer (differentiator, transformation, proof points), and traffic context (source, visitor knowledge)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Context-aware copy dramatically outperforms generic copy. Existing product marketing context eliminates redundant questions and ensures consistency across pages." .

oc:kn_f9aaba97 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing or reviewing any copy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use marketing buzzwords without substance: 'innovative', 'streamlined', 'cutting-edge', 'revolutionary', 'optimize'. Never fabricate statistics or testimonials. Avoid exclamation points, passive voice, and sentences trying to do too much." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Buzzwords erode trust and signal vagueness. Fabricated claims create legal liability. Exclamation points and passive voice weaken persuasive impact." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_1c57a56523ded358 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Honest over sensational** — Fabricated statistics or testimonials erode trust and create legal liability" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_5a3f44ce9e4088a4 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Specific over vague** — Avoid \"streamline,\" \"optimize,\" \"innovative\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_c67c4ddea4b89a38 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Simple over complex** — \"Use\" not \"utilize,\" \"help\" not \"facilitate\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_da56b2643433ea28 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Confident over qualified** — Remove \"almost,\" \"very,\" \"really\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_dea27b4b31c116ab a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Show over tell** — Describe the outcome instead of using adverbs" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_fa4d8ce493246714 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Active over passive** — \"We generate reports\" not \"Reports are generated\"" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_198c82ce85f67d12 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Establish voice and tone: formality level (casual, professional, formal) and brand personality (playful/serious, bold/understated, technical/accessible)." ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Tone guidelines set for consistent copy throughout the page." ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_e403b2e32ceaf8d7 ;
    oc:stepId "establish-tone" .

_:ref_9400b22778f9bca2 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Write core page sections following the page structure framework: Social Proof, Problem/Pain, Solution/Benefits (3-5 key benefits), How It Works (3-4 steps), Objection Handling, and Final CTA with risk reversal." ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Full page body copy structured as a persuasive narrative." ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_c00e9fec7d455cfe ;
    oc:stepId "write-core-sections" .

_:ref_a31b6d82162e6634 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Apply page-specific guidance based on page type (homepage, landing, pricing, feature, about). Adjust structure and messaging for the specific page context." ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Copy tailored to the specific page type with appropriate emphasis." ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_9400b22778f9bca2 ;
    oc:stepId "apply-page-guidance" .

_:ref_c00e9fec7d455cfe a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "Write above-the-fold copy: headline (using formula from references), subheadline (expands + adds specificity), and primary CTA (action-oriented, communicates value). Provide 2-3 headline alternatives with rationale." ;
    oc:expectedOutcome "Hero section with headline, subheadline, and CTA ready." ;
    oc:stepDependsOn _:ref_198c82ce85f67d12 ;
    oc:stepId "write-above-fold" .

